cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object pose estimation from RGB-D images. It may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as accurate object pose estimation is crucial for robotic manipulation tasks. The use of learning-based models suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on exploiting object model priors and generating point clouds suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
